      • getLineVectorSpecifiedSize

        public java.util.Vector getLineVectorSpecifiedSize(int line,
                                                   int indexStart,
                                                   int indexEnd)
        By the given line , detach data from the dataHolder(line) raw string and separate sub-data into vector points by given range. Start use as offset where to indexStart to recipient data, and indexEnd where to stop.
        Parameters:
        line - Specify column from the data vector.
        indexStart - Where indexStart to catch data.
        indexEnd - End of catched data, also doesn't have any limits.
        Returns:
        Provide vector with separated sub-data that was defined in specified range 'indexStart-/indexEnd' to do that.
